Interface ALU_Operations

All Known Implementing Classes:
ALU, ARC_Simulator
public interface ALU_Operations

Names and numeric codes for ALU Operations, as given in Figure 6-4 of the Murdocca and Heuring text.

Version:
$Revision: 1.3 $
Author:
C. Vickery

Field Summary
static byte ADD
          1000 - Add A operand and B operand; do not chaqnge condition codes.
static byte ADDCC
          0011 - Add A operand and B operand; update condition codes.
static byte AND
          0101 - AND A operand and B operand; do not change condition codes.
static byte ANDCC
          0000 - AND A operand and B operand; update condition codes.
static byte INC
          1101 - Add 1 to the A operand.
static byte INCPC
          1110 - Add 4 to the A operand.
static byte LSHIFT10
          1010 - Shift A operand left 10 places.
static byte LSHIFT2
          1001 - Shift A operand left two places.
static byte NOR
          0111 - NOR A operand and B operand; do not change condition codes.
static byte NORCC
          0010 - NOR A operand and B operand; update condition codes.
static byte OR
          0110 - OR A operand and B operand; do not change condition codes.
static byte ORCC
          0001 - OR A operand and B operand; update condition codes.
static byte RSHIFT5
          1110 - Shift A operand right 5 places, filling on the left with copies of the sign bit.
static byte SEXT13
          1100 - Result is bits 0:12 of the A operand, sign extended.
static byte SIMM13
          1011 - Result is bits 0:12 of the A operand padded left with zeros.
static byte SRL
          0100 - Shift A operand left using the value of the B operand as the shift amount.
